\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf2 Drum. Enter BRUTUS, LUCILIUS, LUCIUS, and Soldiers; TITINIUS and PINDARUS meeting them
\f0\i0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Stand, ho!\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 LUCILIUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Give the word, ho! and stand.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 What now, Lucilius! is Cassius near?\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 LUCILIUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 He is at hand; and Pindarus is come\
To do you salutation from his master.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 He greets me well. Your master, Pindarus,\
In his own change, or by ill officers,\
Hath given me some worthy cause to wish\
Things done, undone: but, if he be at hand,\
I shall be satisfied.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 PINDARUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 I do not doubt\
But that my noble master will appear\
Such as he is, full of regard and honour.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 He is not doubted. A word, Lucilius;\
How he received you, let me be resolved.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 LUCILIUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 With courtesy and with respect enough;\
But not with such familiar instances,\
Nor with such free and friendly conference,\
As he hath used of old.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Thou hast described\
A hot friend cooling: ever note, Lucilius,\
When love begins to sicken and decay,\
It useth an enforced ceremony.\
There are no tricks in plain and simple faith;\
But hollow men, like horses hot at hand,\
Make gallant show and promise of their mettle;\
But when they should endure the bloody spur,\
They fall their crests, and, like deceitful jades,\
Sink in the trial. Comes his army on?\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 LUCILIUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 They mean this night in Sardis to be quarter'd;\
The greater part, the horse in general,\
Are come with Cassius.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Hark! he is arrived.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf2 Low march within
\f0\i0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 March gently on to meet him.\
