\f0\i0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 CASSIUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Stand, ho!\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Stand, ho! Speak the word along.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 First Soldier\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Stand!\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 Second Soldier\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Stand!\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 Third Soldier\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Stand!\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 CASSIUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Most noble brother, you have done me wrong.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Judge me, you gods! wrong I mine enemies?\
And, if not so, how should I wrong a brother?\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 CASSIUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Brutus, this sober form of yours hides wrongs;\
And when you do them--\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Cassius, be content.\
Speak your griefs softly: I do know you well.\
Before the eyes of both our armies here,\
Which should perceive nothing but love from us,\
Let us not wrangle: bid them move away;\
Then in my tent, Cassius, enlarge your griefs,\
And I will give you audience.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 CASSIUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Pindarus,\
Bid our commanders lead their charges off\
A little from this ground.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Lucilius, do you the like; and let no man\
Come to our tent till we have done our conference.\
Let Lucius and Titinius guard our door.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf2 Exeunt
\f0\i0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf2 SCENE III. Brutus's tent.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf2 Enter BRUTUS and CASSIUS
\f0\i0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 CASSIUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 That you have wrong'd me doth appear in this:\
You have condemn'd and noted Lucius Pella\
For taking bribes here of the Sardians;\
Wherein my letters, praying on his side,\
Because I knew the man, were slighted off.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 You wronged yourself to write in such a case.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 CASSIUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 In such a time as this it is not meet\
That every nice offence should bear his comment.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Let me tell you, Cassius, you yourself\
Are much condemn'd to have an itching palm;\
To sell and mart your offices for gold\
To undeservers.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 CASSIUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 I an itching palm!\
You know that you are Brutus that speak this,\
Or, by the gods, this speech were else your last.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 The name of Cassius honours this corruption,\
And chastisement doth therefore hide his head.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 CASSIUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Chastisement!\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Remember March, the ides of March remember:\
Did not great Julius bleed for justice' sake?\
What villain touch'd his body, that did stab,\
And not for justice? What, shall one of us\
That struck the foremost man of all this world\
But for supporting robbers, shall we now\
Contaminate our fingers with base bribes,\
And sell the mighty space of our large honours\
For so much trash as may be grasped thus?\
I had rather be a dog, and bay the moon,\
Than such a Roman.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 CASSIUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Brutus, bay not me;\
I'll not endure it: you forget yourself,\
To hedge me in; I am a soldier, I,\
Older in practise, abler than yourself\
To make conditions.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Go to; you are not, Cassius.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 CASSIUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 I am.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 I say you are not.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 CASSIUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Urge me no more, I shall forget myself;\
Have mind upon your health, tempt me no further.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Away, slight man!\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 CASSIUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Is't possible?\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Hear me, for I will speak.\
Must I give way and room to your rash choler?\
Shall I be frighted when a madman stares?\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 CASSIUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 O ye gods, ye gods! must I endure all this?\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 All this! ay, more: fret till your proud heart break;\
Go show your slaves how choleric you are,\
And make your bondmen tremble. Must I budge?\
Must I observe you? must I stand and crouch\
Under your testy humour? By the gods\
You shall digest the venom of your spleen,\
Though it do split you; for, from this day forth,\
I'll use you for my mirth, yea, for my laughter,\
When you are waspish.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 CASSIUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 Is it come to this?\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 You say you are a better soldier:\
Let it appear so; make your vaunting true,\
And it shall please me well: for mine own part,\
I shall be glad to learn of noble men.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 CASSIUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 You wrong me every way; you wrong me, Brutus;\
I said, an elder soldier, not a better:\
Did I say 'better'?\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 BRUTUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0 \cf2 If you did, I care not.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 CASSIUS\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

